The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as question answering and summarization, which are typically covered under the arXiv category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of learning-based methods also suggests a possible fit under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to understand and process text, which could fall under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval tasks, which could fit under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to process and analyze text, which could fit under the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
